OL,3,CLabour highlight 'Martyn's Law' by
OL,4,Ccommitting to anti-terrorism
OL,5,Clegislation
OL,7,FThe new legislation aims to improve
OL,8,Fprotection against terrorism in public
OL,9,Fplaces.
OL,11,FThis includes improving security
OL,12,Fagainst terror threats, training staff
OL,13,Fwith free online training provided by
OL,14,Fthe government, and a requirement that
OL,15,Fall venues have a counter-terrorism
OL,16,Fplan.
OL,18,FUnder the proposals, there will be
OL,19,Fdifferent requirements for premises,
OL,20,Fbased on the number of people they can
OL,21,Fhold.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/11
